From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 02 Jun 2026
Subject: [PATCH] muxer/libav: don't report a muxer error on normal client disconnect

Streaming an MP4 (libav muxer) profile and then switching channel / closing the
player logged "Stop streaming ..., muxer reported errors" every time, while the
same action on a Matroska profile did not. Cause: lav_muxer_write() increments
m_errors when the write() to the client socket returns short, but -- unlike the
pass and mkv muxers -- it never sets m_eos. The webui only suppresses the
"muxer reported errors" warning when m_eos is set (webui.c). MP4 is fragmented
(frag_duration=1) so it is almost always mid-write when the client disconnects
and trips the short write; MKV writes in ~1s cluster bursts and usually isn't,
which is why the warning looked MP4-specific. It was cosmetic (the stream had
already ended because the client left) but misleading.

Fix: mirror the pass/mkv muxers -- on a short write, if errno is a disconnect
(MC_IS_EOS_ERROR: EPIPE/ECONNRESET) flag m_eos so the webui stops quietly. Real
write failures (e.g. ENOSPC while recording) still count as errors and warn.

--- src/muxer/muxer_libav.c.orig
+++ src/muxer/muxer_libav.c
@@ -72,9 +72,17 @@
   }
 
   r = write(lm->lm_fd, buf, buf_size);
-  if (r != buf_size)
+  if (r != buf_size) {
+    /* A failed write to the client socket on a normal disconnect (EPIPE/
+     * ECONNRESET) is an end-of-streaming notification, not a muxer fault.
+     * Flag it as EOS like the pass/mkv muxers do, so the webui stops quietly
+     * instead of logging a misleading "muxer reported errors". Real write
+     * failures (e.g. ENOSPC while recording) still count without m_eos. */
+    if (MC_IS_EOS_ERROR(errno))
+      lm->m_eos = 1;
     lm->m_errors++;
-  
+  }
+
   /* No room to notify about errors here. */
   /* We need to complete av_write_trailer() to free */
   /* all associated structures. */
